From Tom McConnell Subject Re Motif Athena In article David Hughes writes Andrew Berry writes Ports of Motif to both and Linux are available for a fee of about This is cost recovery for the person who bought the rights to The activity in both the BSD and Linux news groups pertaining to Motif has been I just wonder if this will also cause a divergence between commercial and non commercial software you will only get free software using Athena or OpenLook widget sets and only get commercial software using the Motif widget sets I can't see If just about every workstation will come with Motif by default and you can buy it for under for the free UNIX platforms I can't see this causing major Let me add another of my concerns Yes I can buy a port of Motif for cheap but I cannot get the source for cheap hence I am limited to using whatever X libraries the Motif port was compiled against at least with older versions of I have been told that Motif can be used with any X but I have not seen it myself Currently I have running on eight different unix platforms of which only three came with On those three I am unable to use the libraries to build Motif clients because I get link errors between the vendor supplied port of Motif and my I anticipate having this same problem when becomes The result is that I cannot build Motif clients that rely on since I do not have Motif compiled under True I could buy another port of Motif but that sort of ruins the whole idea of free doesn't it Cheers Tom McConnell Tom McConnell Internet Intel Phone Chandler The opinions expressed are my No one in Chandler AZ their right mind would claim